			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">what other classes were in your group? or was it a raid? its easy to blame the warrior but i'm willing to bet that there's more to it than the warrior not taunting.
<br />

<br />
Warrior aggro is a fragile thing that takes time to build. Warrior's don't have quick taunt capabilities. Also, if you're fighting a mob that requires defensive the warrior has lost more taunt due to reduced damage output. You may not have pulled the aggro off the warrior, it may have been the ranger, who then cinder jolted to shed aggro and moved you to the top of the list before the warrior could get his aggro reestablished. It might have been a monk who FD'd to shed aggro and put you at the top of the list. It might have been a rogue who just evaded to shed aggro from a successful backstab. 
<br />

<br />
The taunt button by itself is inadequate anyway. First the taunt has to succeed. Second, a successful taunt will move the warrior to the top of the hate list , but only just barely. If a warrior is already at the top of the hate list then repetetive mashing of the taunt button is useless as the hate gained from taunt isn't cumulative. 
<br />

<br />
There's plenty of discussion on the current state of warriors and taunt here: <a href="http://www.steelwarrior.org/" target="_blank">http://www.steelwarrior.org/</a><br />_________________<br />Ragash Iggytamer
<br />
Exiled Primalist of Grobb</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
