			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">You know what though, Vecsus is right.  A warrior's only reason for existence is to hold aggro and take all the hits that a mob can dish out and keep a mob from jumping around from person to person.  If a warrior isn't doing that, then they're not doing a good job.  That doesn't mean that the warrior is entirely at fault, some good reasons have been given already as to why a warrior may lose aggro.
<br />

<br />
In a cross post from another topic, I suggested a spell line for Shaman that they could cast and imbue warriors(MTs) with a proccing spell (just like we cast on our warders but with hate increasing taunt).  The spell proc would stack with weapons procs.  I know chanters have some spells that they can cast on tanks that have procs, but that line of spells doesn't seem to stack with many of the better raid buffs.   
<br />

<br />
I came up with the thought because even in my guild, it seems like I steal aggro from from the MT a little too often even when I take great care to not steal aggro away from the MT.  I wished that SOE provided more ways for a warrior to hold aggro.  That's all they have.  If the MT doesn't have aggro, there will be unnecessary deaths and that opens the door for a raid wipe out.  Anyway, that's just one idea from a sometimes-lucid person.
<br />

<br />
Skratchen Myitchin
<br />
60 Vah Shir Savage Lord</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
