				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Vecsus wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">when you see the message: "You will not evade me Vecsus" followed by "XXX Rampages on Vecsus".</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Am I the only one who noticed that he is talking about RAMPAGE?  The definition of rampage as I have always understood it is:  When the mob rampages it gets to hit the person currently targeted and 1 additional target.  The mob establishes a list of targets (Rampage List) and rampages the same target until dead. 
<br />

<br />
This is the reason most guilds establish rampage tanks by having 5 or 6 plate meele attack before everyone else.  This ensures that rampage is absorbed by tanks and not other classes.
<br />

<br />
In the case of grind mobs rampaging its just something you have to deal with.  It is not a taunt problem as far as rampage is concerned.<br />_________________<br />Rhugan
<br />
60 Beastlord of Rodcet Nife</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
