			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Rampage list is in order of who gets on the hate list first, second, etc.  It has nothing to do with taunt or how much damage you do after that.  (And <span style="font-style: italic">nothing</span> will move you up or down the list.  Don't rez someone who died to rampage if the mob is still alive - that person will still be on the top of the list.)
<br />

<br />
Most MT's who played a lot in Luclin will try to make sure the <span style="font-style: italic">secondary</span> tanks (usually another Warrior or the Paladin or SK) are first on the rampage list, because the damage spike can get you killed and your group/raid killed, if the healers aren't on the ball.  This isn't laziness, it's good strategy.  Assuming the secondary tanks can survive a rampage, they'll have plenty of time to be healed when rampage ends.
<br />

<br />
This may not be good strategy in PoP,  if the secondary tanks can't survive a rampage - but it probably isn't laziness.
<br />

<br />
*edit*
<br />
Okay, forgot - Memblur can wipe the Rampage list.  This is a bad, bad idea though, unless everyone's prepared.  That Druid who had a heal going off when the memblur happened isn't going to do well near the top of the list.<br />_________________<br />Grimgrey Dorfeater
<br />
Troll Wildblood
<br />
Undivided Faith
<br />
Drinal</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
