			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Well, sort of.  It's who got on the hate list, in chronological order.   Bards tend to end up pretty high on the list unless they stop playing while the pull is happening, the instant a bard song affects the puller the Bard is on the list.  If Vecsus was trying to pre-slow (which I doubt, he has more experience than to do that to a rampage mob) he'd most likely be the second person on the list after the puller, first if the puller was feigned at the time the Rampage went off.
<br />

<br />
Part of my explanation in the previous post was inaccurate, actually - in most circumstances, the person on the top of the normal Aggro list (hopefully the MT) doesn't take Rampage damage.  Head to <a href="http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior" target="_blank" class="postlink">http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior</a> for a better explanation than mine.
<br />

<br />
Oh, and I understand PoP mobs can AE rampage.  I haven't seen that personally, thank god.<br />_________________<br />Grimgrey Dorfeater
<br />
Troll Wildblood
<br />
Undivided Faith
<br />
Drinal</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
